Change has been successfully rebased and submitted as 9bb6ec2bd32d93c8d27efd8c664ff96288c795f2

I suspect this should be an exposes record.  There are other daemons that might want information from this, and putting it in the exposes record allows that to happen.

Also, it means that we can have more consistent rules.  The "BMC" is something than an object can expose, similar to if the object had a TMP75.
Changed to an Exposes record. Updated change https://gerrit.openbmc.org/c/openbmc/entity-manager/+/56769 such that each "Exposes BMC" record also creates a BMC inventory item. Does this look good?
looks like you changed "ContainsThisBMC" to just "BMC".  I think we've lost some of the description in the parameter here.

I changed "ContainsThisBMC" to "BMC" when moving the json object from the root of the board .json file to the "Exposes" section, because "ContainsThisBMC" sounds a bit unnatural in the "Exposes" section.

Some names for retaining the description I can think of are "ContainedBMC", "OnboardBMC". Maybe there are other better ones?
Friendly ping: I think "BMC" fits better in the Exposed section. Is "losing some of the description" still a concern in the "Exposes" section?
I agree within Exposes, "Contain" seems implied, BMC itself is sufficient.
